Figure 2 presents DPV (Differential Pulse Voltammetry) curves recorded in a TiO2-free electrolyte. In voltammograms, there are visible changes of cathodic current density related to the reduction of nickel complexes. Electrogravimetric studies performed in this system show the course of reduction reaction in the same potential range as was previously reported.[38] Based on the current density changes at E = − 1.2 V for several values of the magnetic field induction vector (B) (Figures 2(a) through (c)), the i=ζ(ν1/2)\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
